        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-03-11T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-03-11T22:00:00-05:00" n="38" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P.W./3–1245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-03-12T10:00:00+07:00">March 12, 1945—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 15—7 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>411. French Ambassador told me last night he had information that Langson had
                    been captured by Japs, that there was street fighting progressing in Hanoi, and
                    that in Moncay a French garrison of 1,000 with 20 officers was still holding
                    out. (ReEmbs 403, March 11, 11 a.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d38fn3">Not
                        printed.</note>) He said he did not yet know whether any French troops had
                    endeavored to cross into China. Some time ago he had approached the
                    Generalissimo with regard to that possibility and Chiang had said that French
                    troops would be welcomed and assisted. Ho Ying-chin has recently made a similar
                    statement, but he himself was doubtful whether any definite plans for receiving
                    French refugee soldiers in China had been worked out or would prove very
                    effective.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
